The paper deals with power control and interference management in a wireless network, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of massive MIMO and D2D communication also suggests that the paper could belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SY) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents analytical results and optimization techniques, which are typical of the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
